column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel. British Museum. exhibition of Sung & Yuan painting from Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, 22 Cloudy Mountains by Fang Tsung-I (c. 1300-1378) Shows winding river with aerial perspective of mountains in right foreground with strong dark brushstrokes - like Bruegel. Generally the winding river (Bosch, Patinr, etc.) in Chinese painting much earlier than in Europe (perhaps maybe coming from China to Europe) also the stress on rocks (Bruegel, Valckenborch) and plant in foreground (Vienna Way to calvary) probably derived from East.</content>
